messages.message: :car: :camera_with_flash: Thought I'd share a cool usecase of AI Hub build with all of you. A student who attended one of our workshops used build to create an automatic number plate recognition app - https://www.linkedin.com/posts/jashan-panwa_engineering-gratitude-inspiration-activit[â€¦]42627895297-bT5o/?utm_source=share&utm_medium=member_android (https://www.linkedin.com/posts/jashan-panwa_engineering-gratitude-inspiration-activity-7105588242627895297-bT5o/?utm_source=share&utm_medium=member_android)
this is awesome from accuracy perspective because these images are quite low quality and blurred, however it is still able to extract it correctly :instabase:
I'm not sure out OCR is optimised for usecases like this, but it works decently. Curious to hear from the Reader team about this too @Hari @Rakesh
My former employer did this pretty well, but they also sold cloud storage security cameras.
I do find it cool that the students attending these workshops are getting inspired and building things, though!
Typically we need 300 dpi for best OCR extraction. MSFT OCR works pretty decently with lower quality images too.
